Market Analysis and Size

With the introduction of automation and robotics in recent decades, production lines all over the world have undergone significant transformations. High levels of competition, as well as an increasing emphasis on reducing turn around time, have pushed manufacturers all over the world toward automation in order to maintain high levels of throughput and efficiency.

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the multilayer flexible packaging market was valued at 147.69 million in 2021 and is expected to reach the value of USD 211.64 million by 2029, at a CAGR of 4.60% during the forecast period of 2022-2029.

Market Definition

Multilayer flexible packaging is a method of packaging products that uses non-rigid materials, allowing for more cost-effective and customizable options. It is a relatively new method in the packaging market that has grown in popularity due to its high efficiency and low cost as it uses little material and can be made from chemically recycled material.

